						<summary>

						<p>On the mutilated base of an octagonal pillar found in the village.</p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanachakravartin Kulōttuṅga Chōḷa II (?), A.D. 1155.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1[0*?]77, uttarāyaṇa Sankrānti. (= A.D. 1155 (?)).</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary and damaged. Seems to refer to Āchārya Śrīvallabha of Uṇḍavelli, who is described as <hi rend="italic">Tribhuvanaguru</hi> and as a recipient of some gift (details lost).</p>						

						</summary>
